yzed for our models. The $v_{s}^{2}$ shows that the noninteracting and\nnonlinear interacting THDE with Ricci cutoff will be stable in the past era,\nunstable in the present, and progressive epochs. Then, we will employ the\n$Jerk$ ($J$) and $OM$ parameters to distinguish between our models and the\n$\\Lambda CDM$ model. Finally, we will calculate the age of the Universe for the\nTHDE and nonlinear interacting THDE with Ricci as the IR cutoff.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Nov 2022 18:00:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 8 Dec 2022 12:42:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-09"}
